of prey: from antelopes and warthogs to mice and  
even beetles. 
 
As the most adaptable of the large cats, leopards do  
well in a variety of habitats, ranging from desert to  
mountain to forest. Although the leopard can do  
without a ready source of water, it requires some  
amount of cover. The African leopard can often be  
found in wooded areas of the savannah. 
 
Leopards are excellent climbers and are very much at  
home in trees, where they rest while surveying their  
territory. They also retreat to trees when threatened  
